<br>
The log clearly shows that the parry chain beserkers gets needs to be boosted. In all other accounts it prooved that the beserker does far more damage, and takes a lower percentage of his total hits per mob then a shadowblade. <br>
<br>
He did try to even out the damage by using the level 50 poison, however I do not think that is a fair test. Not every shadowblade will have access to the level 50 envenom, and they may not be using it all the time. I would much rather be doing a high base damage without having to worry about envenoming weapons during rvr.<br>
<br>
I play a level 41 shadowblade with heavy left axe specialization. After fighting side by side with beserkers for a while, and looking at many beserker logs, I can honestly say they are better tanks/fighters then shadowblades are by far. The main thing a shadowblade has going for him is he can stealth. This allows him to have a greater chance of surviving on the battlefield.<br>
<br>
Just my two cents.<br>
Merry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/1/02 2:48:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do shadowzerks compare to zerks?</span><hr size=1> Yes, that's true, studded is weak vs. crush, leather is strong vs. crush.  And they were probably blue at the time, leading to much more damage avoidance by the assasin.  As a 39 healer, I'm very comfortable with having a zerker as the main tank.  I'm not at all comfortable with seeing a shadowzerk tank.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwolvenspikefeather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolven Spikefeather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/1/02 3:26:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do shadowzerks compare to zerks?</span><hr size=1> I never said that shadowzerkers are better tanks then zerkers are.  They aren't.  But, the comparison was a general one.  Against even con solo opponents, the shadowzerker is comparable.  The high level of evades combined with non-stop comeback/frostygaze is a lethal combination.  Right now my wife and I are soloing spindels.  She frequently kills the yellow con's with 0-1 hit taken from her.  Once she gets the first evade off, comeback/frostygaze (which also increase her defense and make more evades more likely) and usually another set of them from more evades.  She mows through them with ease, often killing the orange con ones with out much trouble.  Admittedly spindels are easy kills, but still.  <br>
<br>
In a group, a real zerker is a much better tank, able to take much more of a beating.    In the end game, ie RvR, the shadowzerker wins hand down though due to stealth and poisons.  They can pick their fights and attack with surprise. <p>Wolven Spikefeather, Hunter<BR>Wolvan Ebonmyst, Shadowblade<BR>Blargo; Healer.  Sledgh; Thane <BR>Percival-Guardians of Niflheim<br>Friar,Therguist,Cleric: Nimue<br>Mentalist, Warden: Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umerry11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merry11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/6/02 9:40:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do shadowzerks compare to zerks?</span><hr size=1> Spindels are another bad example. They are the main shadowblade leveling creatures. They have extremely low hit poitns due to their snare spell. They also do not hit hard at all, and with thier minus for leather its even worse.<br>
<br>
Try fighting scavs or even crabs. Crabs hit a lot harder then spindels, and have a lot more hit points. The beserker will start outperforming the shadowblade on those. <br>
<br>
I group with a beserker friend of mine a lot, I might evade more then him, but he does a lot more damage then I do. I rarely ever take aggro from him. He also doesnt have to worry about taking aggro, if I take aggro its two hits I am dead. While he can tank fairly well.<br>
<br>
I do notice when I use my str/con debuf and envenom poison we are pretty close to damage output. However that gets pretty costly for me to use. I spend roughly 20 gold per buble in poisons.<br>
<br>
At any rate, shadowzerkers do less damage then beserkers, have less hits, and get hit harder by just about everything. We get poisons, the ability to stealth, climb walls, and safefall. I do not care what people say I really like safefall!<br>
<br>
For my play style I enjoy my shadowblade. I like scouting, I like climbing keep walls, etc. I do have to pick my fights carefully in rvr, which with my stealth I can do. My beserker friend is not so lucky. <br>
<br>
Merry <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showPrevMessage?topicID=154.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showNextMessage?topicID=154.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.emailToFriend?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.threadControl?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<opt